cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with building discriminative representations for 3D data using neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR) research. The use of machine learning algorithms to optimize the probing points and their locations suggests a focus on optimization and learning (cs.LG), while the use of adaptive distribution in 3D space suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
